# Macro Roadmap Discipline

Treat `plans/MACRO-ROADMAP.md` as the repo's permanent whole-project roadmap.

## Update Required For

- Meaningful phase completions or status changes
- Changes to whole-project sequencing or likely-next work
- Durable assumptions or constraints that alter the long-range plan
- New numbered plans that materially redirect scope

## Expectations

- Read the macro roadmap before non-trivial planning or implementation work.
- Non-trivial plans should include a `Macro Roadmap Alignment` section with roadmap IDs.
- Do not implement directly from the macro roadmap; pull work into `plans/active/Plan-XXX-*.md`.
- If the roadmap no longer matches repo reality, update it before handoff.
